---
// English privacy policy page (LEGAL-03 / LEGAL-05): identical content and
// layout to src/pages/confidentialite.astro (see that file's frontmatter
// comment for the full D-01/D-02/D-03/D-04/D-05 rationale); only import
// depth and copy differ. Slug is deliberately identical to the FR page
// (04-RESEARCH.md Pitfall 1) — getSwitcherHref() only strips/re-adds the
// "/en/" prefix, it does not translate slugs.
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy — Atelier Jacqueline Suzanne">
  <div class="legal-page">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>
      This page describes, simply and directly, the only data handled by this site: contact-form
      data, the site's own content, the host's technical logs, and a single functional cookie.
      This is not a formal legal document — it is a plain-language explanation of what actually
      happens.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact form</h2>
    <p>
      When you send a message via the contact form, it is sent directly to Romane Lepont's own
      mailbox, hosted with OVH, with no third-party processor involved.
    </p>
    <p>
      Data controller: Romane Lepont / Atelier Jacqueline Suzanne, email:
      contact@atelierjacquelinesuzanne.fr.
    </p>
    <p>Purpose: replying to your enquiry.</p>
    <p>Legal basis: your consent — submitting the form is a voluntary action on your part.</p>
    <p>
      Required fields: name, email, and message are required so we can reply to you. An additional
      hidden field (a "honeypot") is used only to detect spam robots — it never collects any data
      about you.
    </p>
    <p>Recipient: Romane Lepont only — no third-party processor is involved.</p>
    <p>Retention: your message is kept only as long as needed to reply to you, then deleted.</p>
    <p>
      Your rights: you have the right to access, rectify, erase, and object to the processing of
      your data. You may also lodge a complaint with the CNIL (the French data protection
      authority).
    </p>

    <h2>Site content (Sanity)</h2>
    <p>
      The site's content (galleries, text) comes from a content management system (Sanity),
      queried only when the site is built. No data about you is ever sent to Sanity.
    </p>

    <h2>Hosting logs</h2>
    <p>
      Like any web host, OVH automatically logs your IP address and browser (user-agent) as a
      normal part of serving the site's pages. This counts as personal data under GDPR, even
      though this site's own code never touches it.
    </p>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      This site uses a single cookie, named <code>ajs_locale</code>. It is only set when you
      explicitly click the FR/EN language switcher — never automatically on page load — and it
      stores only your language preference (French or English). It is set with the{' '}
      <code>SameSite=Lax</code> and <code>Secure</code> attributes, for a duration of about one
      year.
    </p>
    <p>
      This cookie is strictly functional: it is only used to personalize the site's display in the
      language you choose. As such, it is exempt from consent under CNIL guidance — which is why
      this site shows no accept/reject cookie banner. This site uses no advertising, analytics, or
      tracking cookies of any kind.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-2xl) var(--space-md);
  }

  .legal-page h1 {
    container-type: inline-size;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 12cqi, 6.5rem); /* Display role */
    font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-xl);
  }

  .legal-page h2 {
    font-size: 20px; /* Heading role */
    font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin: var(--space-2xl) 0 var(--space-md);
  }

  .legal-page p {
    font-size: 16px; /* Body role */
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-md);
  }

  .legal-page .placeholder {
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>
